The paper deals with the integration of a planning mechanism into sequence-to-sequence models using attention, which is a popular topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Reinforcement Learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The model is end-to-end trainable using primarily differentiable operations, which is a characteristic of deep learning models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of fewer parameters, which is a common concern in neural network models, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of character-level translation tasks and question generation from text, which are tasks related to computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
